import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='speed', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    median_speed = data['speed'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_speed, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_speed:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Convert wind direction to radians
    data['dir_rad'] = np.deg2rad(data['dir'])

    # Create a polar plot
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(subplot_kw={'projection': 'polar'})
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['dir_rad'], data['speed'], c=data['speed'], cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)

    # Set title and legend
    plt.title('How does wind direction vary across the dataset?', wrap=True)
    cbar = plt.colorbar(scatter, ax=ax, pad=0.1)
    cbar.set_label('Wind Speed')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='dirCat', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind direction categories?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Direction Categories')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Wind Direction Categories', loc='upper right', labels=data['dirCat'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
